                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1875">Mare</persName>confronted<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2284">Justinian</persName>and<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/779">Theodora</persName>concerning the persecution. Because of his words and dress, they esteemed him a holy man, and gave him a hundred weight of gold, which he promptly threw away.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/anchorites http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/persecution http://syriaca.org/keyword/justice http://syriaca.org/keyword/emperors http://syriaca.org/keyword/kings http://syriaca.org/keyword/wealth http://syriaca.org/keyword/dress http://syriaca.org/keyword/poverty http://syriaca.org/keyword/polemics http://syriaca.org/keyword/blame"/>
