            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/828-19" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Feeling guilty about the hundredweight gold,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/779">the queen</persName>sent her chamberlains several times to<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1875">Mare</persName>to seek his forgiveness.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/anchorites http://syriaca.org/keyword/shame http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/civil-servants"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/828"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">432</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">634</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/828-20" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Many began to flock to<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1875">Mare</persName>for a blessing, and they were amazed at his prayer and dress. <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1875">Mare</persName>refused to eat anything that was not produced by the labour of his hands.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/anchorites http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/food http://syriaca.org/keyword/fasting http://syriaca.org/keyword/bread http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/blessing http://syriaca.org/keyword/pilgrimages http://syriaca.org/keyword/dress"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/828"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">433</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">635</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/828-21" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            Observing the holiness of<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1875">the man</persName>, Satan encouraged robbers to abuse him, under the impression that<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/799">the queen's</persName>chamberlains were bringing him gold.<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1875">Mare</persName>overtook his assailants by stealing their weapons and attacking them. A chamberlain brought the weapons to <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2284">Justinian</persName>and<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/779">Theodora</persName>.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/anchorites http://syriaca.org/keyword/violence http://syriaca.org/keyword/wealth http://syriaca.org/keyword/justice http://syriaca.org/keyword/demonology"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/828"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">435</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">637</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div type="factoid" uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/828-22" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
